#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn67"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn67:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 67 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 67 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn67:0.2"
msgid "Cātumasutta "
msgstr "At Cātumā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli1.457, sc1
msgctxt "mn67:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn67:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā cātumāyaṃ viharati āmalakīvane. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Cātumā in a myrobalan grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn67:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sāriputtamoggallānappamukhāni pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni cātumaṃ anuppattāni honti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "Now at that time around five hundred mendicants headed by Sāriputta and Moggallāna arrived at Cātumā to see the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn67:2.2"
msgid "Te ca āgantukā bhikkhū nevāsikehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodamānā senāsanāni paññāpayamānā pattacīvarāni paṭisāmayamānā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "And the visiting mendicants, while exchanging pleasantries with the resident mendicants, preparing their lodgings, and putting away their bowls and robes, made a dreadful racket. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn67:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda, "

msgctxt "mn67:3.2"
msgid "“ke panete, ānanda, uccāsaddā mahāsaddā, kevaṭṭā maññe macchavilope”ti? "
msgstr "“Ānanda, who’s making that dreadful racket? You’d think it was fishermen hauling in a catch!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:3.3"
msgid "“Etāni, bhante, sāriputtamoggallānappamukhāni pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni cātumaṃ anuppattāni bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "And Ānanda told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "mn67:3.4"
msgid "Te āgantukā bhikkhū nevāsikehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodamānā senāsanāni paññāpayamānā pattacīvarāni paṭisāmayamānā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn67:4.1"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, mama vacanena te bhikkhū āmantehi: "
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, in my name tell those mendicants that "

msgctxt "mn67:4.2"
msgid "‘satthā āyasmante āmantetī’”ti. "
msgstr "the teacher summons them.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:4.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied. He went to those mendicants and said, "

msgctxt "mn67:4.4"
msgid "“satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti. "
msgstr "“Venerables, the teacher summons you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:4.5"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:4.6"
msgid "“kiṃ nu tumhe, bhikkhave, uccāsaddā mahāsaddā, kevaṭṭā maññe macchavilope”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, what’s with that dreadful racket? You’d think it was fishermen hauling in a catch!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:4.7"
msgid "“Imāni, bhante, sāriputtamoggallānappamukhāni pañcamattāni bhikkhusatāni cātumaṃ anuppattāni bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "And they told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "mn67:4.8"
msgid "Teme āgantukā bhikkhū nevāsikehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodamānā senāsanāni paññāpayamānā pattacīvarāni paṭisāmayamānā uccāsaddā mahāsaddā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5
msgctxt "mn67:5.1"
msgid "“Gacchatha, bhikkhave, paṇāmemi vo, na vo mama santike vatthabban”ti. "
msgstr "“Go away, mendicants, I dismiss you. You are not to stay in my presence.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:5.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya pakkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied those mendicants. They got up from their seats, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right. They set their lodgings in order and left, taking their bowls and robes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, pts-vp-pli1.458, sc2
#. VAR: santhāgāre → sandhāgāre (mr)
msgctxt "mn67:6.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena cātumeyyakā sakyā santhāgāre sannipatitā honti kenacideva karaṇīyena. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Sakyans of Cātumā were sitting together at the meeting hall on some business. "

msgctxt "mn67:6.2"
msgid "Addasaṃsu kho cātumeyyakā sakyā te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante; "
msgstr "Seeing those mendicants coming off in the distance, "

msgctxt "mn67:6.3"
msgid "disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "they went up to them and said, "

msgctxt "mn67:6.4"
msgid "“handa kahaṃ pana tumhe āyasmanto gacchathā”ti? "
msgstr "“Hello venerables, where are you going?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:6.5"
msgid "“Bhagavatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhusaṃgho paṇāmito”ti. "
msgstr "“Sirs, the mendicant Saṅgha has been dismissed by the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:6.6"
msgid "“Tenahāyasmanto muhuttaṃ nisīdatha, appeva nāma mayaṃ sakkuṇeyyāma bhagavantaṃ pasādetun”ti. "
msgstr "“Well then, venerables, sit here for a minute. Hopefully we’ll be able to restore the Buddha’s confidence.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:6.7"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū cātumeyyakānaṃ sakyānaṃ paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sirs,” replied the mendicants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7
msgctxt "mn67:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho cātumeyyakā sakyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho cātumeyyakā sakyā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then the Sakyans of Cātumā went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn67:7.2"
msgid "“abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ; "
msgstr "“May the Buddha approve of the mendicant Saṅgha! "

msgctxt "mn67:7.3"
msgid "abhivadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ. "
msgstr "May the Buddha welcome the mendicant Saṅgha! "

msgctxt "mn67:7.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, bhagavatā pubbe bhikkhusaṃgho anuggahito; evameva bhagavā etarahi anuggaṇhātu bhikkhusaṃghaṃ. "
msgstr "May the Buddha support the mendicant Saṅgha now as he did in the past! "

msgctxt "mn67:7.5"
msgid "Santettha, bhante, bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ. "
msgstr "There are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. "

msgctxt "mn67:7.6"
msgid "Tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr "If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "mn67:7.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, bījānaṃ taruṇānaṃ udakaṃ alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ siyā vipariṇāmo; "
msgstr "If young seedlings don’t get water they may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "mn67:7.8"
msgid "evameva kho, bhante, santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya alabhantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr "In the same way, there are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "mn67:7.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, vacchassa taruṇassa mātaraṃ apassantassa siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo; "
msgstr "If a young calf doesn’t see its mother it may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "mn67:7.10"
msgid "evameva kho, bhante, santettha bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, tesaṃ bhagavantaṃ apassantānaṃ siyā aññathattaṃ, siyā vipariṇāmo. "
msgstr "In the same way, there are mendicants here who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training. If they don’t get to see the Buddha they may change and fall apart. "

msgctxt "mn67:7.11"
msgid "Abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ; "
msgstr "May the Buddha approve of the mendicant Saṅgha! "

msgctxt "mn67:7.12"
msgid "abhivadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ. "
msgstr "May the Buddha welcome the mendicant Saṅgha! "

msgctxt "mn67:7.13"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, bhagavatā pubbe bhikkhusaṃgho anuggahito; evameva bhagavā etarahi anuggaṇhātu bhikkhusaṃghan”ti. "
msgstr "May the Buddha support the mendicant Saṅgha now as he did in the past!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli1.459, sc3
#. VAR: samiñjitaṃ → sammiñjitaṃ (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn67:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati bhagavato cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito bhagavato purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati knew what the Buddha was thinking. As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn67:8.2"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9
msgctxt "mn67:9.1"
msgid "“abhinandatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ; "
msgstr "“May the Buddha approve of the mendicant Saṅgha! "

